inn1.comm: encouraging carry! Back of a length and outside off, left alone
better carry! Qdk takes it in front of his face. Short and lifts outside off, zippy stuff. Ignored again
back of a length and angled in on top of off at 145ks, Charles blunts it to the covers
much fuller and outside off, trickles away to the boundary. Charles presses forward and slices the drive through the covers and point. Not middled, but four. Charles exploits the shorter boundary
full and swerving in to ping the front pad, but it was slipping down the leg side
145ks short and moves away outside off, Charles has a feeble waft and watches the ball whistle past the outside edge. Sharp first over
pitched up and angling away, guided gently towards point
Fletcher flies out of the blocks! Overpitched just outside off, smeared to the left of long-on, even as the bat twisted in his hands

Morkel into the action, at deep third man, for the first time this series?. He runs to his right, slides, and parries the ball to the boundary. Short and width outside off, comes on nicely, as the captains said at the toss. Slashed away
rears up from a length outside off and swings away a bit, the batsman has a bigger swing at it and misses
very full on off and cuts away outside off, Fletcher drops his bat late and is beaten again

Fletcher has another swing and nicks off. SA find an early breakthrough. Perfectly pitched, this. Full and angled away wide outside off. The opener chases it with a flashy drive and edges it behind to Qdk. Healthy nick. Gone...
Rabada puts this on a back of a length on off, defended
back of a length and swerves in at 143ks to ping the batsman below the rib cage
just missed the off stump! Full, shoots low, does not bounce at all. Charles has a loose drive at this 147ks ball and is beaten

Rabada now strikes! This one bounces and takes the outside edge near the higher part of the bat. 146ks. Good variations. Back of a length and put on off, Charles has a lazy waft. No feet movement. He is late to loosen his grip. He ends up feeding an outside edge to Morris at second slip

bowled'em! Make that two in two. Rabada is pumped. Scorching yorker at 146.3ks/90.9mph, swings in as well, Samuels is late to bring his bat down. Timbaaah! The off stump is floored. All three batsmen guilty of being pinned to the crease....
errant one down the leg side, although he touched 140ks, wide
outswinger on a length outside off, draws the drive and passes the outside edge. Crackin' over
length and outside off, left alone
full inswinger, deflects off the thigh fine, to the right of Qdk
full angled in and straightens past the outside edge of this loose prod. Bravo not moving his feet too
short and zings through outside off, Bravo spars at it. No feet again. Passes the outside edge
full on middle, Bravo was camping back, anticipating a shortish one. He drops it in front of his feet
tight, tight leave! Back of a length and tantalisingly close to the off stump. Bravo isn't quite sure about his off stump. SA teasing the hosts in Barbados
full and aimed at the base of middle and leg, squirted back to the bowler
full and angled in on middle, Ramdin gets his feet moving. Presses forward and pushes it to mid-on
back of a length and outside off, guided to the covers. FB swoops down on the ball and denies the single
similar length and sliding down leg, Ramdin uses the angle and finds an escape route. Glides it fine past Qdk for four

140.2ks, Ramdin ducks into a lifting ball and is pinged on the helmet. Banged in short and angled in, Ramdin was probably a bit late. He took his eyes off the ball and is socked on the grille. Replays show that it bounced up off the shoulder to the grille. Nasty blow

Rabada softened up Ramdin and makes the incision. The middle stump is floored now. Scorching pace. 149ks 149.5ks to be precise. Yorker again angled in. Ramdin is late to flick it across the line, possibly to midwicket. Not great shot selection. Might have grazed the pad before demolishing middle
Bravo is uncertain in the channel. Full and outside off, he is late to draw his bat away. Wafts it past the cordon
pitched up and outside off, forward and solidly pushed into the covers
good length and angled in on middle, Bravo probably misjudged the length. Ends up camping back and poking to cover
Parnell snatches the outside edge but it does not carry. Morris dives to his left at second slip. Taken on the bounce. Bravo only had a weak prod at it
full on middle, stays back and keeps it out
fuller and around off, run down to third man via an open face
good length and angling away outside off, Bravo goes searching for it and is beaten by bounce
142.3ks. Edged and wide of the slip cordon. Bravo was opened up, sparring at it
but this isnt short, back of a length and angled down leg, glanced away off the thigh for four, fine on the leg side
back of a length and angled in, KP leans into a front-foot block
prancing short ball. Banged in on middle, has Pollard ducking out of the way
back of a length on off, Pollard is forward to smother it
full and angled in, Bravo is right behind it to defend
full incoming ball, which is wafted towards square leg for a quick single
full and aimed at off, Pollard responds with a front-foot push to mid-off
bouncer down the leg side, KP ducks under it. Wide called for line
good length and attacking off again, Parnell is at least 10ks slower than Rabada. KP has enough time to press forward and blunt it towards the covers
full and swerves in on off, clipped through backward square leg. Not an emphatic stroke, though
full, very full at the legs, stylish whip to long leg. Probably, the first emphatic shot from Bravo this afternoon
inauspicious start, slants a length ball down leg. Wide
good bounce, tighter line. Full and outside off, Bravo hoists his bat above his shoulder and leaves
banged in short and outside off, left alone on length
lifting short ball, homing in on the chest at 139ks, Bravo hops and drops his bat down. Hits the shoulder and the ball dies in front of slip
full and around off, bunted to the covers for one
full and attacking the stumps, pushed to mid-on
lifts from a back of a length, Pollard is surprised. He loosens his grip and manages to fend it gingerly in front of the covers. Lively stuff from Morkel
full and outside off from over the wicket, Bravo gets forward and plays a solid push to mid-off
Morris' turn to bang it short, outside off, Bravo hops, skips, and fends it to the covers
too full and outside off, push-driven to the left of mid-off
too full and on the off stump, Pollard cashes in the cheque. Whipped away smartly through square leg on the front foot
full incoming ball on the off stump, fluent drive to mid-on, diving save to his right from Faf. Sharp work
back of a length and outside off, Pollard reverts to leaving action
short on middle from round the stumps, Bravo leaps and fends to the leg side

Parnell misjudges the catch at the long leg boundary. He moves to his right, leaps, was wary of the rope, ends up parrying it over the boundary for six! Banged in short and outside off, late to hook. Bravo sent a top edge and Parnell shelled it as he went over the ropes. Perhaps, Parnell did not need the jump and lost his balance
Morkel sends down another short ball and roughs Bravo up. He aims to work to the leg side and gives a leading edge in front of the covers
back of a length and outside off, left alone
fractionally short and outside off, Bravo rocks back and controls a pull wide of mid-on
back of a length and angled in at off stump, Bravo hops and blocks back to Morne
skids on full on middle, milked to long-on
full and flighted outside off, Bravo unleashes a clean swing and puts Tahir over long-on. Lofted with authority
Tahir whirls down a quicker one down leg
googly, full and dips on middle, run towards the covers
flat and fired on middle, squeezed out to the covers
hurled on middle 91ks, played back to Tahir
full and outside off, fluent drive to long-off for one
short and angled into the thigh, Bravo keeps back and tucks a single through square leg
back of a length, skiddy ball on off, KP loosens his grip and cushions it to the off side
length ball on off, wafted to short midwicket off the inside half
short on middle, fended to the left of FB at short leg
leaping short ball on middle, Pollard yanks his bottom hand off the bat as he rides the bounce, fended this time to the right of short leg
overpitched and outside off, Bravo slices a drive and dispatches it to the square boundary
googly, rips back in, sharp one. Pollard did not pick it and took it on the thigh
another attempted googly? Dropped short on middle, pulled to deep midwicket
off-stump full toss, flowy drive to the right of long-off. The fielder chases, and slides in vain
tossed outside off, may have been a wrong'un. Outside edge runs past lone slip
legbreak on middle, worked to short midwicket
flat and dips on middle, skewered towards point
back of a length and angled in, blocked towards point. Solid...
pitched up and outside off, Bravo steps forward and drives it crisply through the covers. AB chases and hunts the ball down
full and angled in on middle, guided towards point. Morne has overstepped by a substantial margin
Bravo moves away outside leg, Morne goes short and wide outside off. Sails over the head. Morne has to bowl it again

full and bang on middle, Bravo, having backed away, slams an inside edge onto the side of the left knee. He grimaces and hobbles for the single. After completing it, Bravo went down. He attempted an almighty slog and hurt himself. The physio is out. Magic spray time
pitched up and outside off, KP attacks it. He plants his front leg forward and muscles the loft. Hit through the line over long-off for six

edged and finds the gap between wide slip and Qdk. Full and outside off, KP pokes and nicks it close to the left of Amla at wide slip. He could not get a hand, despite a dive. Sneaks away to the third-man fence
good length and around off, bunted gently towards point
full on off, flowy drive to short extra cover
bouncer, ducked under carefully, wide called for height
even fuller and outside off, Bravo laces a drive to sweeper cover. Stylish....
full and on off, right in the slot. KP plants his front foot forward and punches it over mid-on who was inside the circle. Calculated hitting
full toss, swerves in on middle, picked away to the backward square leg boundary. Morris is leaking runs as well
strike three! overpitched on off, KP strides forward and drills a drive past the diving short extra cover fielder. The crowd finds its voice at Barbados. 100 up for the hosts
length and outside off, stabbed towards point
angled in full on off from over the wicket. Defended on the front foot
incoming ball on off, poked towards short midwicket via an inside edge. Hurried single
short and on the thigh, KP misses the flick as the ball rolls to the leg side
full on off, Bravo goes across the line as he shovels it over midwicket for another boundary
short and wide outside off, lashed straight to mid-off
short on off, turned to square leg for one
full and angled in on off, blocked to leg
rising short ball on off, KP is caught in a tangle. Manages to fend it softy towards point
here comes KP, couple of paces forward. Morris shortens his length and pings the pad. The ball rolls behind square on the leg side
full and angled away outside off, no shot offered
back of a length and close to off, cramps the batsman for room, mis-times to short extra cover
back of a length and outside off, angled away, Bravo chases and nicks it through the vacant cordon
back of a length and angled into KP from round the wicket, nudged to mid-on for a quick one

pitched up and outside off, Bravo flows forward.... beautiful. Driven through the covers. Mid-off had no chance. Holder applauds Bravo's fifty. Only fitting that Bravo got to the landmark with a drive
good length and put on off, dabbed towards point
prancing short ball just outside off, effort ball from Parnell. Bravo is up to the challenge, sways his upper body out of the way
length and outside off, Bravo dabs a single to third man
KP uses the incoming angle and clips a single to long leg
full and straight, clipped behind square on the leg side
short and kicks up outside off, fended to backward point
back of a length on off, KP loosens his grip in defence
another short one rears up outside off, KP rides it down to third man. A tighter line could have cramped KP up
full and angled away outside off, smartly steered down to third man
KP targets the leg side and ends up leading-edging this length ball in front of short extra cover
legbreak on a length, blocked back
skiddy ball, poked to backward point
quicker leg-stump ball, glanced to backward square leg
looks like a googly, drifts in, Pollard prods from the crease and misses
slider on middle, Pollard hangs back and drops it in front of his feet
full and on off, nudged behind square on the leg side
back of a length, wicket-to-wicket line, blocked
short, leg-stump line, leaves Bravo in a tangle. Rapped on the glove as the ball rolls to point
banged in on middle, Bravo jumps and defends
pitched up on middle, clean drive to mid-off. His drives have been stylish
full and attacking the stumps, slower one, 123ks, blocked back
banged in short, leg-stump line, surprises the left-hander and raps the glove
overpitched and outside off, driven to long-off
tossed on middle, blocked
full on middle, pushed to the off side
pitched up on middle, quicker one, blocked back
much slower through the air, blocked back again
length and angled in, KP comes forward and blocks it solidly
banged in short and angled in, KP drops his gloves and sways out of the way
full toss outside off, KP drills it back to the bowler. Rabada was more looking for evasive action instead of going for the catch. That was smashed back
change-up, slower and outside off, check-pushed to the covers
rising short ball outside off, KP rises with it and rides it to point
leg-side wide
dug in short and outside off, the wide hurts KG and SA. Bravo reaches and flays it up and over backward point, beats the fielder in the deep
full on middle, wrong'un, nudged to midwicket
another wrong'un. KP picks. Goes back and drops it in front of his feet
flat and straight, clipped to short midwicket
flighted on middle, slogged to long-on. Dragged off the inside half
googly outside off, goes back and flashes an outside edge, does not carry to short third man
slapped from outside off through the covers for four
back of length delivery on off, chopped down to third man
angles one full on middle stump, bunted back to the bowler
lofted through the line, one bounce into the boundary! Jeez, it was loaded with risk, but Bravo ensured he was hitting with a straight bat. Beautifully done, the swing did the trick for him there

width on offer, and he's crunched that into the cover boundary. This is even better. There's a hint of width, he presses half forward and belts that into the vacant spaces. Hand-eye coordination at its very best
floats one down leg side, wrong line, more work for the umpire

he's dealing in boundaries here. Over the wicket, around the stumps, it doesn't matter. Poorly bowled again. This is a length ball on off stump, and it's sitting up nicely for Bravo to loft through the line over cover, couple of bounces into the cover boundary
gets a thick inside-edge on a drive to mid-on
looks to go over long-on, gets a thick inside edge to deep midwicket. The ball spun a touch more than Pollard anticipated there
fired into middle from around the wicket, defended back down the pitch
slider down leg, Bravo misses a faint tickle, collected cleanly by QDK
clean, crisp drive against the turn to deep cover. He did well to get to the pitch of the ball there to negate the spin
pushed through quicker, hint of drift into middle, turns away as well, Pollard is solidly behind the line of the ball
driven back to the bowler, who stops it well on his followthrough
driven down to JP Duminy at long-on, sensible cricket this
banged in short, Pollard fetches the pull from outside off to deep square. There were cries of caaaaaaaatch, but it landed well short of the man there
uses the pace to run that one down to third man
gets forward and negates the incoming delivery with a dead bat

through the gate, and didn't miss the off stump by much. Peach from Morne. Slides this one back in from wide of the crease, the ball pitches on middle and holds its line, Pollard is beaten as he plays outside the line. Saved by the bounce
drifting down leg, tickled to fine leg for an easy single
nips back in from outside off, Bravo watches it through to the keeper
flatter one on middle and leg, whipped off his hips into the vacant spaces at deep square leg. Muted celebration to his fifty.  Ninth ODI fifty  for him
whipped again, but there's Morne at short fine to cut that off

in his slot, and he's given it a good thwack. What's worse? It's a no-ball. So  free-hit  to add insult to injury. Too full, all Pollard had to do was extend his arms and bring his big biceps into play as he muscles that. Not much of a follow-through of the bat, but wow, that flew into the stands or what
looked to go over cover, ends up slicing it over backward point, races away into the short boundary that side
spins back into middle and leg, worked wide of Morkel at short fine for an easy single
slider gone wrong, not much turn there as it goes down leg
beaten on the drive, it wasn't there for him to play the shot. First poor stroke he's played in a while
waits for it to spin away as he taps it to short third man
what's happening here? Another wide. Morkel's clearly looking undercooked here as he spears in another wide down leg side
bunted to backward point, shouts 'noooo' almost immediately
extra bounce on that one as Pollard is hit on the thigh pad while trying to nudge it to the leg side, they scamper through for a leg bye
another shocker, this one's on the seventh stump down the leg side, wonder if the umpire's arms are sore
another short one outside off, steered to point
slower one on the pads, he directs it wide of midwicket for an easy single

there's the breakthrough, and it's come against the run of play. The crowd is stunned, what a shame! Morkel delivers a full ball angling into middle, Pollard uses his wrists to whip it over the infield. Such was his confidence that he was prepared to take on the man in the deep, but Faf made no mistake. He kept his eyes on the ball, moved a couple of paces backwards to set himself up and then timed his jump to perfection to pull off that rocket hit! Pollard smashes his pads in disappointment. West Indies were running away with it, but will have to rebuild again. Relief more than elation in the South African camp
length ball angling away, runs it down to third man
gets a thick inside-edge to midwicket
solidly behind the line of that length ball on off stump
drives but the ball tails back in late to lob off the inside edge, one bounce to midwicket
crunching sound as ball met bat, straight to cover though
that's a scorcher. Banged in short on middle from wide of the crease, Holder drops his wrists and sways out of the way
he's welcomed with a biff down the ground. For a while, it looked like long-on would be in business, but the ball just kept sailing over. Saw the flight and went through with it. Straight as a dye
gets forward and eases it gently to the off side
a touch short, he makes room and cuts it straight to point
gets to the pitch of the ball and defends to the off side again
worked with the spin to midwicket, the over has kept getting flatter and flatter
what's he trying to do there? I'm not sure. Looks to swing across the line, but is clearly beaten by the wrong'un that rips back in to hit his pad
play and a miss. Looks to run it over the vacant slip cordon but is late on the shot
short ball, testing the bounce of the surface maybe? Bravo has no trouble in ducking underneath that. That's one bouncer for the over
deceived by the slower one, nearly got sucked into the drive. Fortunately for Bravo, it was angling away and flirting with the wide line

that's flown off the thick bottom edge into the third man boundary. Bisected the keeper and short third man. It was bowled into the blockhole, and Bravo got the bottom edge as he looked to jam his bat down to get that
driven with an opened bat face to deep point
drives the incoming full delivery to mid-on
offers a straight bat to that full delivery, mid-on stops that
short and he's slapped that straight to deep midwicket
flatter one on middle, pushed with the spin to mid-off
sees the flight and goes through with a flat hit down the ground, mid-off stops that
lovely flight again, lands it on off, Holder mistimes a drive to cover. It was too full
this time it's a leg break that is driven with the spin to cover
would have been a dead duck had he missed that. The flatter googly spins back into middle and leg as Holder whips that to midwicket. It kept a touch low as well
hops back to get on top of the bounce and bunt it to the leg side

what a way to get to his  third ODI century!  It's also his first since August 2014. This one was full and angling away, but Bravo decided he was going after it as he swung through the line. The angle meant he ended up dragging it a bit towards wide long-on, but there was enough bat on it for the ball to sail over the ropes. Pumps his fists, celebrates by soaking in the applause of the crowd. Top quality knock this. His previous two tons came against Zimbabwe and Bangladesh
squeezed behind the stumps on the off side for a single
gets half-forward and plays it gently to cover
drives well, but straight to point
looks to flick but can't get any bat on that, is hit high on the pad
width on offer, crunched to deep cover

and it's a misfield that allows Holder to get off the mark finally. He mistimed the pull, but Faf dived in front of the ball. It was hit so hard that the ball still had enough to race away to the boundary despite the deflection.  Has taken Holder 17 deliveries to open his account  Morris applauded Bravo as he walked past him.  Good to see!
gets forward do tap that to cover
eased back to mid-on for a quick single
edged, but doesn't carry to Amla at slip. Not much bounce on this one as Holder looks to steer it wide of point. Good save nevertheless
cuts and misses. Didn't have the width for him to play the stroke
driven down to mid-off to get off the mark
flatter one on middle, Holder is lucky to get away with that as he stabs outside the line to get an inside edge
appeal for lbw, this was the googly. Holder prods forward and outside the line again as the ball lobs off the flap of the pad
too full on off stump, patted back down the pitch
tossed up on middle, firm drive to long-on
somehow manages to slice it over cover. Looked to go on-side, poor shot selection
defended back to the bowler
back of length delivery on middle and leg, worked to midwicket
opens the face of the bat and runs that full delivery down to third man
rip roaring bouncer again! Holder sways out of the way. It was directed towards the body. That's one for the over, says the umpire
and uses the double bluff by slipping in a yorker, but it was tailing down leg, worked to fine leg
gets half-forward and then opens the bat face to squeeze it behind point
slower one on off stump, tapped to cover

was it deliberate? I think, yes. Back of length delivery angling in from around the stumps, Brathwaite opens the bat face late to run it down to third man, got it between the keeper and the wide slip fielder
defended off the backfoot with soft hands
hops back and across as he tucks it down to fine leg
punched into the gap between cover and point. Stands tall, uses the angle to play it off the backfoot to the sweeper
scoring opportunity missed, this was a full toss on middle stump, he turned the bat face early to play it to the on side, the ball rolls off the side of the bat
nicely behind the line of that slower one, defended to the off side
starts off with a slower delivery on middle, Holder works it to AB at mid-on and sets off for a risky single. It was a one-handed pick-up and throw, but wide of the stumps at the bowler's end
sliding down leg side again, flicked to deep midwicket
width on offer, runs it down to third man
uses his height to good effect as he stands tall and punches it to deep cover
gets on top of the bounce and bunts it behind point
this time, he works it to the vacant midwicket region. Another short ball, mind you, but once again he was on top of the bounce as he kept it down to pick the run and keep strike
full and tailing away from off stump, Brathwaite gets a thick edge to gully

a direct hit from backward point at the striker's end, but they take a run off the deflection. Brathwaite was couple of paces outside the crease and was casually stretching back in when JP Duminy's throw hit the stumps, but he was well in
delicately done, opens the bat face late to run it wide of the slip fielder, third man was a touch square as well
backs away and plays the low full toss to mid-off
worked with the angle to midwicket, AB fires a throw at the bowler's end, but Brathwaite was in
poor end to the over. Width outside off, Holder makes a bit of room and slaps the full toss over cover. Degree of nonchalance in that

shot, sir! Carlos Brathwaite has muscled a back of length ball on off stump over the sightscreen. He even posed for the cameras after hitting that, shows you how much he enjoyed that. Stands tall and goes down town with a straight bat. Wow!
this one's squeezed down to Tahir at third man
half-chance for Amla but both batsmen were quick to complete the run. Holder simply dabbed it behind the stumps and took off for the single
excellent bouncer this time, bowled with a cross-seam, Brathwaite ducks under that
second bouncer for the over. This one's just a touch outside off, Brathwaite manages to avoid that again
slips one down leg side, easy call for the umpire
awkward bounce, nearly had him. Bowls it short of  length outside off, the ball hits one of the cracks and then shoots up as Brathwaite is beaten on an attempted dab to third man
solid thump! Sashays down the pitch, makes room and slaps that over cover. Picked the bones out of that one

makes room and eases it to the point fielder who fires a wayward throw at the bowler's end. Have they taken the overthrow? Some confusion there. The ball deflected off Holder, but they went for the second. It wasn't deliberate

magnificent! This boy can bat or what. Takes a couple of steps down the wicket and simply picks that up on length and whips it over deep midwicket. He hit that with the wind and into the short boundary.  New ball please, that one hit the roof and bounced out.
nearly chopped it back onto the stumps
gets a thick inside-edge on the drive to long-on,  words exchanged.  Morris is clearly unhappy with that extra run off the overthrow
gets a leading edge that rolls towards point
flatter delivery on middle and leg, worked wide of square leg
on the pads, worked towards the vacant square leg region again. He's firing them in from wide of the crease
this one bounces off the deck on middle, perhaps the googly which gets big on Brathwate as he looks to defend
stabs forward, gets a bit of inside edge onto the pad as the ball lobs up, but it wasn't anywhere near the keeper
gets back and across to punch that back to the bowler
drifts in a quicker one that is defended with soft hands
full and straight on middle, squeezed to long-on
full toss tailing into the pads, whipped to long-on. Perhaps he wanted to hit it a lot squarer

goes length this time, and Holder's vigil is over. Once again looks to go towards the short boundary by trying a whip over midwicket, only manages to get a thick outside edge that is well pouched by Quinton de Kock!
beaten by late away movement from middle stump
angles it down leg side. This one pitches on the eighth stump or so
cuts and misses. There was width, but Narine was deceived by the lack of bounce
gets underneath that yorker, worked wide of the bowler to long-on

what was Narine trying to do there? I really don't know. He was pushed deep into the crease when he bunted that to Morris, who ran in from point, picked up the throw cleanly and threw down the stumps at the bowler's end. Made it look so easy, and Narine wasn't even in the picture
rip roaring bouncer on middle and off, he somehow gets out of the way
edged to short third man, they scamper through for a single
lovely flick off his pads towards deep midwicket
looks to spear in a yorker but ends up sliding it down leg side as Brathwaite misses a faint tickle
did he get some bat on it? Umpire doesn't signal wide this time even as QDK dives full length to his left to stop that. If he didn't give it wide, surely that had to be out? Strange
hops back to negotiate that short ball, an overthrow at the striker's end from point gives them a run that will keep Brathwaite on strike
drilled down the ground to long-on, looked for a yorker and nearly got it right there

too straight, and he's been punished. Fine leg was brought into the ring at the start of the over, and it's almost poetic that the ball had to go there. Yorker length on the pads, Benn gets some bat on it to beat the man inside the ring. Four welcome runs
lobs off the leading edge, but just short of Amla

is there an appeal for caught behind? Yes! Dharmasena is checking with his partner to ask if it carried. So it was a definite edge there, according to them. The soft signal is not out. And they're right. There was a thick inside edge there, and the ball just fell short of de Kock.

pulled, but he's holed out to deep midwicket. Outstanding catch by Duminy at deep midwicket. Once again the short ball, he fetches the pull from outside off, but the ball gets big on him and lobs high in the air as the fielder runs in, even as the sun was in his eyes, before tumbling forward to take the catch. Benn didn't have to do that. Could that cost them 10 runs in the end?
squeezed down to third man to retain strike
floats a full ball on the stumps from wide of the crease, Brathwaite blocks
scoring opportunity missed, the full toss it hit back to the bowler
keeps one out, this was full and tailing in, Gabriel offers a dead bat

attempted yorker turns into a low full toss, Gabriel gets a thick inside edge towards deep midwicket. It should have been a run-out as Behardien fires a throw at the keeper's end, but de Kocks whips the bails off before collecting the ball. Shabby to say the least
driven down to long-on, the crowd roars for Brathwaite is on strike. They don't take the run. Both batsmen were confused, and were mid-pitch when they decided to get back to their respective ends
swing and a miss. Full and angling away, just toeing the wide line. Harsh maybe? I think so

drilled to long-on where Faf's knees get stuck into the turf as he dives to his left to stop that. Given the high standards he sets for himself, that has to count as a misfield. But make no mistake, that was struck really hard
play and a miss. Slower one outside off from around the stumps, he was too early into a feeble push
swing and a miss. Didn't bounce as much as he expected there, bounces through to de Kock
backs away to pull, but misses. Was through with the stroke way too early

backs away to hit that to mid-off, confusion all around as Gabriel casually strolls down the pitch without realising Amla was backing up from short midwicket. He collides into him as the direct hit is effected at the bowler's end. Poor running. Brathwaite has a word with AB de Villiers, but to be fair, Amla wasn't aware which way the batsman was running as his eyes were trained on the ball. But still, you have to wonder if there was a case for the umpires to get into the thick of things there.

inn2.comm: induces an edge that flies past second slip to third man. Amla was squared up by that lifter from off stump
mistimes an attempted flick to square leg
hops back into the crease to tuck that short ball on his hip towards deep fine leg
floats it full on the stumps from wide of the crease, Amla gets back into the crease and pats it back down the pitch
gets it wrong this time, the ball veers in down leg side, Ramdin stops that on the bounce
short ball angling into middle and leg, worked behind square on the leg side for an easy single
appreciable bounce off the deck on leg stump, Amla hops back to defend
lovely delivery first up, bowls it full on off stump, but Amla's feet are stuck to the crease as he plays outside the line to get an inside edge onto the pad

shelled, and that could be a big moment in the match!  Genuine outside edge as Amla is late on the drive to the away-swinger, and Ramdin was on the move as he stuck his gloves out to take that. Benn also had a chance to take that on the rebound at slip, but he was a touch late to react
gets half-forward to bunt it to the off side
width and he's middled that into the gap behind point. Delightful timing. The fielder also made it a touch easy by diving over the ball
floats it well outside off, around the wide line. Umpires these days are very strict with line calls
lets go a length ball angling in from wide of the crease, he's consistently clocking over 140 kph
this one lifts off the deck from the length area outside off, Amla shoulders arms. As it turns out, an excellent leave
hops back and opens the bat face to ease it down to third man
sliding into the pads, worked to square leg where Kieron Pollard dives to his right to stop that. Swift work
bottom-edges an attempted cut to point. The ball didn't bounce as high as Amla expected
once again he gets on top of the bounce and wrists it to Pollard at square leg
turned the bat face a touch early as the ball lobs to where a short mid-on would have been, no damage done though
uppish, but safe. Lands short of midwicket as they sneak a run in
hustles Amla for pace as he hops back to bunt that to cover
back of length delivery on middle and leg, worked wide of midwicket for a quick single
well, they were vary of him trying to whip. This one's too full, and he's flicked that superbly in front of square. Races away into the midwicket boundary

this time it's a screamer from Ramdin! He was initially moving to his right with the angle of the delivery, but had to suddenly change track as the ball flew off the bottom edge. Ramdin stayed down nice and low, which allowed him an opportunity to swiftly change directions as he pulled off a low catch moving to his right. De Kock is gone, that's a well-deserved wicket for Gabriel. Ramdin let one go in the last over, but has redeemed himself. Gabriel was pleading with the umpire and nearly appealed thrice before Dharmasena's finger went up.
gets half forward before offering a dead bat to that incoming delivery
works it wide of midwicket to get off the mark
opens the bat face late to run that down to third man

mid-on dives over the ball. The big man Brathwaite, the culprit there. It was on the pads, and he flicked it well by rolling his wrists to keep it down. Brathwaite dived over the ball. Poor, poor effort
a direct hit from point from Fletcher and Faf would have been gone.  Amla guides it to point and sets off even before his partner could respond. Faf had no option but to complete the run. Lucky break
solidly defended off the backfoot to the on side
stands tall and punches a length ball to cover
rides the bounce and runs it down to third man
yikes! That kept alarmingly low on off. Faf stooped to keep it out

Gabriel slices Faf into half! The batsman beaten for pace. 148.4ks/92.2mph. A big appeal, and umpire's Brathwaite's finger goes up. Faf has a chat with Amla and takes a review. Sharp inducker, strikes the flap of the back pad. Was there an inside edge? Nope. Pitched in line and hitting the stumps. Would have taken the middle stump. Lbw. Review ends in vain, ump Brathwaite's call is vindicated
excellent short one on the leg stump, cramping the new man for room. He awkwardly fends it towards midwicket
pitched up on off, driven to the covers on the front foot
inswinging yorker on off, 149ks, Amla drops his bat down in time and jams the ball to the covers
full and swerves in, Amla drops it gently in front of midwicket and hustles for the single even as the bowler goes forward and to his right to hunt the ball down
rising short ball on off, Amla rises with it and fends one to the leg side
this burst off a back of a length outside off, skirts past the lazy waft of AB. Just zipped through
skiddy length ball on middle and leg, knocked to the midwicket region
AB rides the bounce of this back of a length ball outside off and secures a single to third man
full and attacking the off stump, blocked out to the covers
full and cuts in on off, Amla shuffles across off in defence
Gabriel rushes AB. Full and zings in, AB stays back and survives, thanks to an inside edge
slightly overpitched and outside off, toe-ends a drive and finds mid-off
back of a length and wide outside off, 140ks, AB reaches out and steers it to KP at gully
full and swings in, punchy drive to mid-off
back of a length and ducks in, hangs back and punches to mid-on

Gabriel beats AB for pace as well! 144.4ks/89.7mph The captain walks back for only two. Full and outside off, AB chases it with a wild drive. He is late to do so. He ends up nicking it behind, Ramdin takes a good catch tumbling to his right. He goes down, landed badly on his right shoulder. He gets some attention from the medical staff. The quick caps a wicket maiden
full and outside off, driven to mid-off on the front foot
Amla is now beaten for the lack of pace. Offcutter from Holder, early into the pull and is hit on the shoulder
rising short ball on off, quicker one, Amla shuffles across and blunts to the midwicket region
Amla is up on his toes, punching a shortish ball from outside off to cover point
back of a length and outside off, Amla runs it to Benn at gully
full and angled in, blocked back, maiden
FB's first ball homes in full on off, he defends to the covers
good length and swerves in, wafts to mid-on off an inside edge
menacing short ball angled in around chest height, the batsman sways his upper body out of the way
fraction short and wide outside off, FB latches onto it, slashing a square-cut to the right of point, First runs after 18 balls
speared wider outside off, left alone now
full and outside off, FB is forced to reach out for a drive. Instead, he dribbles an inside edge to mid-on
full and outside off, wristy drive to the covers
cross-seamer outside off, swing and a miss
length ball on off, Amla shuffles across and dabs to mid-on
FB shuffles across off and guides this back of a length ball to fine leg
Amla walks across the off stump again even before Holder sent this down. The WI captain uses his height to generate extra bounce. Fended
Amla shuffles across off and gets another lifting ball. Fended to the leg side again
drops it gently into the off side for a quick single

Remember, South Africa wasted a review, so Amla can't go up for this lbw appeal. But I don't think there's anything wrong with this. This one's pushed through quicker, the ball drifts back in, pitches on off and skids on. Amla anticipates the one to veer away just a touch and pushes outside the line of the stumps, and was plumb in front once he was hit on the pad. Boy, I haven't seen Narine as animated as that in a long, long time. West Indies on fire!
shapes to cut, this one holds onto the surface but there was enough room for Duminy to cut
mistimes a pull into the vacant spaces at wide long-on, it was lobbed in the air, and there were shouts of 'catch' briefly
gets onto the backfoot and defends
slider down leg, Behardien misses, Ramdin takes it cleanly
punched to short mid-on. Successful over for the hosts
floats a length ball across Duminy, who lets that go
another slider that angles away, Duminy shoulders arms
gets on top of the bounce and bunts it back down to the bowler
hops back and nurdles it to deep square for an easy single, there's some zip here for Holder
pulled, but not entirely in control. It doesn't matter though as Gabriel has made a royal mess at fine leg. Looks to stop it with his left leg, but can't in the end.
pushed straight to gully
short, wide and Duminy crunches that towards deep cover, where Johnson Charles, running around the ropes from long-off, dives across the turf to pull that back in
gets back and across to tap it gently to the on side

through the gate, missed everyone and runs into the boundary. The ball breaks back in sharply to beat the inside edge, Ramdin was somewhat blinded by the bat and the pad, but there's no excuse really for missing that, especially at this level. Handy runs for South Africa
steps out but is beaten in flight as Narine slows it down and holds his length back, the ball lobs off the pad towards short leg. Spurts of excitement from behind the stumps
lunges forward and defends
appeal for lbw, wonder what Behardien was thinking when he attempted a reverse-sweep. Very, very close. Umpire reckons it may have struck him outside the line of the stumps.

the skipper is on fire, the entire team is on fire. Holder's decision to continue bowling while his hamstring his holding up well is paying off. Gets this one to lift off the deck from around the stumps, Duminy is clearly hustled for pace as he hops back to turn it to the on side, and can only get a leading edge that lodges in the bucket hands of Benn at gully. West Indies' celebration tells you a story. This has been an outstanding burst of fast bowling! Kensington Oval is buzzing with excitement
excellent yorker first up, Morris somehow manages to get underneath that and keep it out
gets on top of the bounce and bunts it to the off side
pulled, but not off the middle, Fletcher comes around to cut that off at deep midwicket
gets back into the crease and dabs that one to the off side
rip roaring bouncer, Behardien pulls out of an attempted pull, square leg umpire signals wide as he thinks it was way over the batsman's head. Holder is clearly disappointed with that decision
turns it to fine leg for an easy single
excellent stop by Brathwaite at short fine leg, it was travelling but he dives to his left to stop that
flatter one on middle and leg, turned to the leg side, Pollard puts his hand out to stop that at short leg
forward short leg in business again, the big man Pollard again
turns it with the spin towards midwicket
top-edges a sweep into the deep square leg boundary. Not much control, but he was hitting with the spin into the vacant spaces. Pollard has some choice words for Morris from short leg
cuts, but finds point. Tight over nevertheless
too full on off stump, Behardien looks to play across the line, squeezed to point with an opened bat face
pulled but straight to Charles at square leg
crunched that pull, but there's Fletcher at deep midwicket to cut that off
punched off the backfoot to cover
pulls and misses. The ball gets big on him, also holds up on the surface a touch. Morris was way too early ito the stroke
punched into the gap at extra cover, Samuels gives it chase and pulls it back in
sharp turn back in, Behardien prods outside the line. Big, big appeal but Narine knew it was going down
was there to cut, he makes room and plays it well, but finds the point fielder
worked with the spin to short midwicket. Lot of chatter around the batsmen at the moment
gets to the pitch of the ball and eases it down to long-on

sharp turn, sharp catch. Pollard celebrates as he snaffles that healthy inside edge with his right hand. This one is pushed through quicker from Narine, gets some bite on it as Morris's jab lobs in the air. Pollard does a celebratory run, and then goes towards the boundary and then bows down to the crowd and the dressing room. For a moment, I thought he was doing a Tahir there. South Africa in disarray here.
this one slides back in from around the stumps, Parnell wanted to leave but brought his bat down late to keep that out
wow, brute! This one takes off from the length area on off stump, Behardien hangs his bat out, and is extremely lucky to not get a nick on that one
in the air, but just short of Samuels at cover. He wanted to hit through the line, but the ball stopped on him a bit

not for the first time has Gabriel made a mess of things at fine leg.  Holder beats Behardien in pace, as the top-edge off the pull flies to the man there, and Gabriel's greasy palms and oodles of misjudgment gives South Africa a reprieve
length ball angling across the stumps, left alone
gets on top of the bounce and bunts it to the off side
on the pads, flicked to deep midwicket
steps out, gets to the pitch of the ball and works it wide of mid-on for a quick single
edged, squared up completely as he went onto the backfoot to defend that, just falls short of second slip
gets a leading edge to point as he looks to work across the line
makes some room and punches it to the off side
stays inside the crease to push that full ball to the off side
ugly swipe across the line, beaten by the sharp turn
full on middle, hangs back and keeps it out
back of a length and outside off, wafts and miss. Beaten on the outside edge
full incutter, beaten on the inside edge now
full and outside off, stabbed to the covers
wide line outside off, FB reaches out and carves it away through the covers for a rare boundary
back of a length and kicks up outside off, FB goes searching for it and is beaten
full and drifts in on middle, poked to he leg side
pitched up and outside off, tapped through the covers
offbreak on off, forward and flicked to midwicket
knuckle ball, FB targets the leg side in anticipation of the offbreak. Skews a leading edge through point

an appeal for lbw, not given by ump Brathwaite. WI review. Slides on middle, the left-handed batsman is pinned to the crease as he pushes with a straight bat. Hit in line with the off stump. Tracker shows clipping leg stump. Umpire's call
92ks, knuckle ball pushed outside off, FB plays for the offbreak and is beaten emphatically
full on middle, poked to the leg side
left alone outside off
back of a length and climbs on middle, fended to the off side
full and outside off, angled to gully
Parnell gets forward and pushes this full ball to the covers
stabbed to gully as it was wide outside off
tossed on middle, bunted to long-on
twirled on a length outside off and turns away, round-arm one, outside edged to gully
this one swerves back in, defended
full on middle, kept out
round-armed onto the pads, nudged to square leg for one, despite a mix-up
Narine gives this loads of air. Slower offbreak, FB squirts an inside edge onto the pad
full, turns in and catches the pad
tossed on middle, flicked out to long-on for a jogged single
short and turns away outside off, cut to deep point
looped up and outside off, inside edged to midwicket
spins back in sharply, Parnell steps back and stabs it wide of slip
shuffles across off and blocks to the midwicket region
low full toss on off, pushed back to the bowler
nails a yorker on off, squeezed out
length ball on off, FB clears his front leg and smears it over mid-on
Fletcher shells a difficult chance. Cutter outside off, FB aims to loft and slices it to sweeper cover. The fielder dives forward, and the ball bursts out
angled towards backward point
full and angled in on middle, bunted down to long-on
drifts in and turns away, back of a length, punched to the covers
dipping full toss on off, clipped wide of midwicket
tossed just outside off, Parnell employs the reverse sweep and sends it past lone slip to the third man fence
Parnell presses forward and pushes this full one to midwicket
pushed through flat, blocked to leg side
slider on middle and off, defended back
FB steps out and meets a full ball early. Carved in the air... drops in front of Fletcher at sweeper cover
back of a length on middle, blocked to the covers

short and around off, dabbed to cover point. Parnell wants a speedy single, but is sent back by FB. The fielder gets across from point, takes aim, and misses a direct hit at the striker's end. They ultimately sneak a single via an overthrow

FB holes out. Length and seams away outside off. The batsman goes deep in the crease, swings across the line and toe-ends it. The ball lodges into the hands of Charles, running in from long-on. Bobble. Bobble. Taken on the third attempt
back of a length on middle, defended
back of a length and outside off, slapped to third man
flighted and outside off, Parnell goes low and cracks it to the covers
tossed on middle, worked to midwicket
length ball on middle, turned to midwicket
sharp turn into the left-hander, lbw appeal not given. The tracker shows that it would have bounced over the stumps
floated and outside off, slog-sweeps and top-edges it over backward square leg
tucked off the back foot to midwicket
back of a length and angled in, nurdled through square leg
banged in short on off, Parnell loosens his grip and fends it onto the pitch
full toss on middle, pushed to mid-off
veering into the pads, easily picked away through midwicket
whipped off the pads to deep midwicket
Rabada stands tall to meet this short ball outside off. Forced away through the covers for four. Proper shot
tossed on middle, another reverse sweep past slip. Good execution
Parnell dances out and shovels this one to long-on
spins in on a back of a length, defended on the back foot
more spin, knocked down to long-on
down the track and nearly yorks himself. Jammed to covers
whipped from outside off with the spin, to long-on
round-armish full one outside off, slings in, tapped to the covers
floated on middle, driven straight down the ground
biting offbreak, pitches on off and rips away past the outside edge
and again! Round-arm action, slings in and turns away. Parnell wafts and misses again
strike three! Sharp turn outside off, beaten past the outside edge
flat, non-turning ball on off, pushed back to the bowler
tossed on middle, defended to short mid-on
whipped with the spin to midwicket
shortish and turns in, swivels and pulls towards fine leg
worked off the pads to the midwicket region
down the track, the bowler held this full ball back, check-driven through the covers
down the track and clipped out to long-on

biting offbreak, topples Parnell. Ramdin whips the bails off in a flash and looks confident. Pitched up on and around off and turns away. Parnell pushed out and lost his balance. Is there something behind the line? Tough call for TV ump Kettleborough. Not out is the final call
pitched up and outside off, driven to the covers
Narine has his man now. Round-armish short ball turns away outside off. Extra bounce. Parnell shapes to cut and ends up top-edging a catch to Carter at backward point
tossed on middle, dabbed to backward point
Morne hangs back and defends to midwicket
darted flat, punched through midwicket on the back foot
short on off, clipped to midwicket
worked to midwicket on the back foot
glanced off the pads to fine leg
low full toss on off, pushed to the covers
flat on off, nurdled off the back foot behind square
flighted on middle, defended towards slip
floater outside off, dabbed past the two-man cordon. Morne aims for a quick single but undoes his steps in time
length and outside off, blocked to the covers
lots of flight on middle, Morkel attacks it and lofted down the ground for four
turned behind square on the leg side for one
Narine gets it to rip in, carrom ball? beats the inside edge, beats Ramdin as well. Byes. Replays pick up an inside snick
drifting outside the leg stump, clipped behind square on the leg side
lobbed up on middle, hangs back and defends to midwicket
Benn liberally tosses it up outside off, the batsman slices a drive through the covers
slider on off, blocked
blockhole ball on middle, squirted out to the covers

Nurse claims a catch at leg gully. Out? Umpire Dharmasena sends it upstairs. The soft signal is out. Fair ball, it is. Full and fired into the leg stump. KG sweeps, it bounced in front of the sub fielder, hit the boot, and looped up. The fielder dives and takes it with an outstretched right hand . Replays show that it dropped in front of him
bouncer outside off, Morne ducks his head out of the way
back of a length on middle, blocked back to the bowler

another run-out appeal, sent to the TV umpire. KG is out now. Back of a length and outside off, chopped to backward point. Morne sets off. There is a mix-up. The fielder aims a direct hit and misses. Nurse looks to gather the throw, fumbles, and tags the ball to Ramdin. Caught short
full and angled in, Tahir prods and gets an inside edge onto the pad
full and outside off, pushed to the covers
defended to the covers
whipped to midwicket
slid down leg, wide
Benn gives this ample air outside off, Morkel is tempted into a lofted hit. He clears mid-off for his second boundary
leg-stump ball, helped away past leg gully
floated and outside off, drives and sends an outside edge towards third man
overpitched and outside off, flashed down to long-off

102ks slider outside off, Tahir shapes for a wild cut and edges it to slip Holder actually swerved out of the way and conceded a four. Benn isn't pleased with his captain's effort. He did not even attempt the catch. Took evasive action
pitched up on off, splat! Morne plonks his front foot forward and drills it past mid-off
bouncer, ducked under
short on middle, fended towards point
slower cutter outside off, punched into the off-side gap
first slip - Nurse - dives full-length to his right to stop this outside edge from Tahir
pretty full on middle, pushed to mid-off. Tahir wants a single, but is sent back, after a mix-up. He dives, the throw wasn't direct either
short and turns away outside off, chopped to the covers on the back foot
floated on off, dabbed gently to point
full and aimed at off, defended to point again
whipped from outside off to midwicket as this was shorter
extra bounce outside off, Morne slashes, and the ball misses the outside edge. Excellent carry to Ramdin
Benn lobs this outside off, chipped to the right of the bowler
full ball on the stumps, driven towards long-on
nearly sneaked through Tahir's defense, this one was right into the blockhole from wide of the crease, Tahir somehow managed to get his bat down in time to keep that out
prods forward and dabs it to the off side

tough chance put down!  Tahir arches back to play a fancy upper cut, but can only get a thin edge over Ramdin's head and into the boundary. The keeper leapt in the air but could only get a bit of glove on that
deflects off the thigh pad to the leg side
angles a full length delivery into the pads, Tahir is late on the flick, ball thuds into the pad
punched to short midwicket
tossed up on middle, Morkel gets forward and smothers the spin
shaped to swipe that but changed his stroke in the end, defended to the off side
worked off his hip to deep midwicket
fierce sweep. Is that Tahir's best? This was tossed up nicely, he gets down on one knee and sweeps it behind square
squeezed into the point boundary. This was once again tossed up over Tahir's eyeline, and he came down on that hard to slice it behind square. Benn's frustration is evident
driven firmly to long-off, Morkel walks through to complete the run
slapped off the backfoot to mid-off, some swagger there from Immy

wow, what a shot! Stand and admire. Not much feet movement, but the 'stand and deliver' mantra has earned him another four. This was in the slot, and Tahir went through with that. High elbow that came down in a lovely arc to meet the ball
stops on him a touch, sluggish bounce from middle, Tahir takes the bottom hand off the grip as he defends
solid frontfoot defense this time
driven to short cover, Tahir wanted the run but realised he had hit it a little too quickly to the fielder
skids one across Morkel, who lets that go
whipped to midwicket
gets to the pitch of the ball and bunts it to long-off
nearly sneaked through. This one pitched on off and held its line, Tahir read it late but adjusted well to defend

shapes to cut, and he'll get another boundary. Crunched off the backfoot to Benn, who lets it through his legs. He was frustrated when Holder put down a catch. It's payback time. Holder stares back at Benn, who looks away
sees the width, throws his bat at that and gets a thick edge that flies to the left of point! More agony for West Indies. This is Tahir's highest ODI score
solid defense, shows the full face of the bat to play it back to the bowler
imperious pull in front of square. Fletcher in business at deep midwicket
play and a miss. Too full to play the cut, didn't miss the edge by much
chopped past the slip fielder,  50 partnership up with the first scoring shot that's not a boundary
lovely little on-drive to long-on

that's the end of that! The partnership is over.  West Indies are into the final!  This was angled in from wide of the crease, the ball holds its line as Tahir pokes inside the line. Ramdin takes a regulation catch, much to the relief of his colleagues who have had to toil for the last three wickets. Smiles all around in the West Indies camp
